
=Principles=

The eight principles of regenerative economy are: 

(1) in right relationship; 

(2) views wealth holistically; 

(3) innovative, adaptive, responsive; 

(4) empowered participation; 

(5) honors community and place; 

(6) edge effect abundance; 

(7) robust circulatory flow; and 

(8) seeks balance. 

See: Capital Institute. “8 Principles of a Regenerative Economy.” https://capitalinstitute.org/8-principles-regenerative-economy/. 


